messages.content: You are a harmless gamer. You should play the game like a human rather than a machine. You can talk and play games.

In this game, a proposer selects any number of resources from 10 units to give to a responder. Then the responder accepts or rejects the proposal. If the responder accepts the offer, both parties receive the benefit; if the responder rejects the offer, both parties receive zero benefit.
640 participants must make their decision as both the proposer and the responder.
When acting as the proposer, each participant must decide how many units to take from the pool of 10 to give to the responder. When acting as the responder, they must determine the minimum number of units they will accept before accepting the proposal.
After all participants make their decisions, the 640 individuals are randomly matched and play the game according to their pre-determined choices.
Your goal is to get the maximum benefit possible.

In this game, a proposer selects any number of resources from 10 units to give to a responder. Then the responder accepts or rejects the proposal. If the responder accepts the offer, both parties receive the benefit; if the responder rejects the offer, both parties receive zero benefit.
640 participants must make their decision as both the proposer and the responder.
When acting as the proposer, each participant must decide how many units to take from the pool of 10 to give to the responder. When acting as the responder, they must determine the minimum number of units they will accept before accepting the proposal.
After all participants make their decisions, the 640 individuals are randomly matched and play the game according to their pre-determined choices.
Your goal is to get the maximum benefit possible.

In this game, a proposer selects any number of resources from 10 units to give to a responder. Then the responder accepts or rejects the proposal. If the responder accepts the offer, both parties receive the benefit; if the responder rejects the offer, both parties receive zero benefit.
640 participants must make their decision as both the proposer and the responder.
When acting as the proposer, each participant must decide how many units to take from the pool of 10 to give to the responder. When acting as the responder, they must determine the minimum number of units they will accept before accepting the proposal.
After all participants make their decisions, the 640 individuals are randomly matched and play the game according to their pre-determined choices.
Your goal is to get the maximum benefit possible.

After all participants make their decisions, the 640 individuals are randomly matched and play the game according to their pre-determined choices.
Your goal is to get the maximum benefit possible.

In this game, a proposer selects any number of resources from 10 units to give to a responder. Then the responder accepts or rejects the proposal. If the responder accepts the offer, both parties receive the benefit; if the responder rejects the offer, both parties receive zero benefit.
640 participants must make their decision as both the proposer and the responder.
When acting as the proposer, each participant must decide how many units to take from the pool of 10 to give to the responder. When acting as the responder, they must determine the minimum number of units they will accept before accepting the proposal.
After all participants make their decisions, the 640 individuals are randomly matched and play the game according to their pre-determined choices.
Your goal is to get the maximum benefit possible.

In this game, a proposer selects any number of resources from 10 units to give to a responder. Then the responder accepts or rejects the proposal. If the responder accepts the offer, both parties receive the benefit; if the responder rejects the offer, both parties receive zero benefit.
640 participants must make their decision as both the proposer and the responder.
When acting as the proposer, each participant must decide how many units to take from the pool of 10 to give to the responder. When acting as the responder, they must determine the minimum number of units they will accept before accepting the proposal.
After all participants make their decisions, the 640 individuals are randomly matched and play the game according to their pre-determined choices.
Your goal is to get the maximum benefit possible.
